-- Colombian Stocks: Ecopetrol, Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-05-02T20:49:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/colombian-stocks-ecopetrol-grupo-aval-acciones-y-valores.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 1.6 percent to 15,460.97, while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  gained 1.6 percent to 1,814.12. Local markets were
closed yesterday for a holiday.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
advanced 2.6 percent to 5,850 pesos. First-quarter profit
climbed to 4.27 trillion pesos ($2.43 billion) from 3.11
trillion pesos a year earlier, the company said late April 30.  Ecopetrol aims to increase production to about 850,000
barrels a day at yearend and has overcome first-quarter pipeline
slowdowns, Vice President Hector Manosalva said on a conference
call today with analysts.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores SA  (PFAVAL CB), Colombia’s
biggest banking group by assets, advanced 4 percent to 1,315
pesos. First-quarter profit rose 51 percent to 394.4 billion
pesos, the company reported on the financial regulator’s website
April 30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
